The paper discusses the security of a public key cryptosystem, which falls under the category of Cryptography (cs.CR). The cryptosystem is based on Chebyshev polynomials, which are a mathematical concept related to Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the cryptosystem, which is related to Systems and Control (cs.SI). The attack described in the paper involves algebraic manipulation, which falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the possibilities of constructing public key cryptosystems on real numbers, which is related to Numerical Analysis (cs.NA).
